OL,3,CHow does the UK prepare for floods and
OL,4,Cextreme weather?
OL,6,FBetween 1961 and 1990, London and
OL,7,FHampshire were the only places to
OL,8,Faverage six or more days over 28C.
OL,10,FBut in 2023, that rose to 20 days
OL,11,Facross 11 different counties in the
OL,12,Fsouth and east of England.
OL,14,FThe number of "extremely wet" days was
OL,15,F20% higher in the most recent decade
OL,16,Fthan in the 60s, 70s and 80s.
OL,18,FMarch, July, October and December 2023
OL,19,Fwere all in the UK's top 10 wettest
OL,20,Fmonths ever, according to records
OL,21,Fwhich go back to 1836.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/15
